section.para:
			The example below embeds a minimal 5x7 PNG as a data URI:

String text = "An image data:image/png;base64,"
    + "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUAAAAHCAYAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA"
    + " follows.";

AssetDetector detector = new CursorAssetDetector();
EmbeddedAsset asset = detector.detect(text).get(0);
// asset.format()        = "png"
// asset.mediaType()     = "image/png"
// asset.width()         = 5
// asset.height()        = 7
// asset.decodedLength() = 45
byte[] bytes = asset.decode(text);  // the original 45 bytes

			The asset's span covers the whole URI; its payload span covers just the
			base64 characters, and decode reads them straight from the
			original text.
			AssetsManualExampleTest asserts the behavior shown here.
